node.text:
5 rounds
30 seconds burpee 
30 second jump squats 
30 second pike push ups
30 second  half walk outs 
60 second rest

Hit that link in the bio to get your spot for my 30 day Full body HIIT challenge. This program going for its final round tomorrow Monday April 26. Hit the link in the bio to save your spot before it closes tonight.

Enjoy over 50 body weight exercises with modifications, written along with video instructions, meal planning, an accountability group of other challengers, and mobility exercises all at home.

Look out for the new challenge coming soon!

How do you stay motivated?

I’m asking this question because it’s a question a lot of people ask me. At this point in my journey what I do is embedded in me, it is a regular habit so not to do it would feel unfamiliar to me. My advice to anyone that needs help staying motivated I would say:

1️⃣ Set a goal and make sure it’s a goal that interest you and is realistic 

2️⃣ Share with someone who likeminded so that you have someone that holds you accountable and so your not alone

3️⃣ Track your progress not only so you can see how far you have come but so you can see areas of weaknesses that need your undivided attention 

4️⃣ Be patient with yourself and trust yourself
 
5️⃣ Find a way that won’t interfere with your goal to reward yourself 

6️⃣ Trust the process 

Stay locked in! It’s you against you. It won’t be easy but if you really want it all you have to do is fight through.

#functionaltraining #dmvtrainer #staymotivated #getupandmove #plyometrics #plyometricstraining #fullbodyworkout

node.text:
Happy Monday!

Getting back to grind with the start of a new week. Hit mobility, glutes, and core for today’s work. I’m trying out some new things to bring about some new  results. Elevation is the goal this week. I’m only looking to get better!

Outfit: @myfitbymoefit

node.text:
Happy Friday!

Well my plan was for it to be one until my coach for the day @d.butlerfit chose violence over peace. 😂😂😂 

Seriously it was good work as usual and it felt good getting back in the groove of things after dealing with horrible unexpected IBS flare ups this past week. I’m grateful to be on my two feet and pushing through. Happy Friday enjoy your weekend, be safe, and have fun!

What’s your favorite body part to  train and can you guess mine?

It was a heavy Glute and Ab day the other day. Got in and got out! We’re halfway through the week keep taking steps towards your goals and overcoming all the things that you thought you would never do.

#gluteworkout #abworkout #workoutmotivation #workoutoftheday #train

My time is now!

If you speak it you shall receive it go into this week with a changed mind. Everything you want and need is within your grasp you just have to reach out and grab it. I’m super excited for this month, the new beginnings, and all blessings to come.

Decided to knock out upper body early in the week because it’s the one thing that I can honestly say challenges me.

Want to get quick a but effective workout in in 20 mins or less?

Then save these moves tag your workout buddy and let me know how these go.

Five exercises 
Complete all five exercises no rest 
After you finish all five 60 second rest
Then repeat for five rounds 

If you’re ready for some high intensity workouts that will bring you maximum results in 30 days all at home with no equipment necessary my 30 day full body burn program is going for another round. The challenge begins Monday August 1, 2021. 

The program will include
	•	4 weeks of intense workouts 
	•	Over 50 different exercises 
	•	An accountability group 
	•	Written and video instructions 
	•	Meal planning 

 Spots are limited so be sure to hit the link up above and lock in your spot

Outfit: @myfitbymoefit

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Monique Collier on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and shorts.

node.text:
“Better is the end of a thing than it’s beginning, and the patient in spirit is better than the proud in spirit.”

Ecclesiastes 7:8-14

And I’m far from finished!

Keep growing and keep glowing

Here’s to Monday!

One thing that I know is that discomfort is the key to growth. Facing difficult situations head on allows you to grow in so many areas especially when starting your route to success. There will be humps, bumps, and holes along the way that might set you back but always be willing to learn from them so you can dodge them and know what to look for if you ever have to circle back. Acknowledge the problem, hold yourself accountable, but also give yourself grace. No one is perfect. You are more than worth it, set your pace, and always run your own race!

This Quad workout took me out but what I will gain will be so much better than the soreness and temporary pain

Outfit: @gymshark

Full body Friday!

Save this one for your next full body session. 

Grab two kettlebells my weight of choice was 25lbs.
Knock out each move 10 reps each
5 rounds 
Knock em down

node.text:
And when life hits hard sometimes you must hit back 10x harder.

Told myself let’s get up!

node.text:
Less talking more working brings about progress for certain!

Focused on the things I can control and allowing God to handle the rest. Moving this body while I’m able and pushing myself to be my absolute best.
